### Workflow - Token Transfer APIs (v1)
### B2C: RETAIL_TRANSFER_CREATE / C2C: OWNER_TRANSFER_CREATE / Accept: OWNER_TRANSFER_ACCEPT

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json
@retailAccessToken = REPLACE_RETAIL_ACCESS_TOKEN
@ownerAccessToken = REPLACE_OWNER_ACCESS_TOKEN
@consumerAccessToken = REPLACE_CONSUMER_ACCESS_TOKEN
@tenantId = REPLACE_TENANT_ID
@passportId = REPLACE_PASSPORT_ID
@transferId = REPLACE_TRANSFER_ID

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────
### B2C Transfer Flow (Brand/Retail → Consumer)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1) Create B2C transfer (QR)
# @name createB2CTransferQR
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/tenants/{{tenantId}}/passports/{{passportId}}/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{retailAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "acceptMethod": "QR",
  "expiresAt": "2026-03-04T00:00:00Z"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("transferId", response.body.transferId);
  client.global.set("qrNonce", response.body.qrNonce);
%}

### 2) Create B2C transfer (CODE)
# @name createB2CTransferCode
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/tenants/{{tenantId}}/passports/{{passportId}}/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{retailAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "acceptMethod": "CODE",
  "password": "transfer1234",
  "expiresAt": "2026-03-04T00:00:00Z"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("transferId", response.body.transferId);
%}

### 3) Accept B2C transfer (QR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/transfers/{{transferId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{consumerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "qrNonce": "{{qrNonce}}"
}

### 4) Accept B2C transfer (CODE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/transfers/{{transferId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{consumerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "password": "transfer1234"
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────
### C2C Transfer Flow (Owner A → Owner B)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5) Create C2C transfer (QR)
# @name createC2CTransferQR
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/passports/{{passportId}}/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "acceptMethod": "QR",
  "expiresAt": "2026-03-04T00:00:00Z"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("transferId", response.body.transferId);
  client.global.set("qrNonce", response.body.qrNonce);
%}

### 6) Create C2C transfer (CODE)
# @name createC2CTransferCode
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/passports/{{passportId}}/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "acceptMethod": "CODE",
  "password": "mySecret99",
  "expiresAt": "2026-03-04T00:00:00Z"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("transferId", response.body.transferId);
%}

### 7) Accept C2C transfer (QR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/transfers/{{transferId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{consumerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "qrNonce": "{{qrNonce}}"
}

### 8) Accept C2C transfer (CODE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/transfers/{{transferId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{consumerAccessToken}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "password": "mySecret99"
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────
### Cancel Transfer
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 9) Cancel transfer (C2C: owner / B2C: retail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/workflows/transfers/{{transferId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerAccessToken}}
